<ul class="project-title-and-text">

    <li class="project-title">
        Slap
    </li>

    <li class="project-type">
        Product / Packaging Design
    </li>

    <li class="project-tools">
        Photoshop, Illustrator, Figma
    </li>

    <!-- <li class="project-objective-title">
        Objective
    </li>

    <li class="project-body-text">
        To create a package and product design for a canned drink.
    </li> -->

    <li class="project-objective-title">
        About
    </li>

    <li class="project-body-text">
        Slap is a citrus-flavored energy drink available in four flavors: lemon, key lime, mandarin, and grapefruit.
        The name came from the sharp sourness that citrus hits you with. The color palette pulls directly from the
        fruits
        themselves: citrus has a bright taste that's almost aggressive, and the packaging needed to match that energy on
        a
        crowded shelf filled with competitor brands. The die line was designed as a single sheet to simplify assembly
        and reduce production costs.
    </li>

    <!-- <li class="project-process-title">
        Process
    </li>

    <li class="project-body-text">
        The name "Slap" is attributed to the bite of sourness from citrus fruits that is akin to getting
        slapped in the face. The logo and images of sliced citrus fruit have a pixelated appearance to embody 
        the sharp taste of citrus fruits. There are also plus sign images, representations of the energy boost 
        received after consuming the drink. The die line of the package is a single sheet, making it easy for assembly 
        and for commercial shipping in large amounts. The package has a tab lock top and a crash lock bottom. The 
        four-color citrus slice present on both the top and bottom of the package represents how each pack holds a 
        variety of four different flavors.
    </li> -->
</ul>

